@Node Intro "Introduction - Miami Start/Stop - Miami Online/Offline/Online Details/Program Launcher with GUI"
@{fg highlight}@{b}Introduction:@{ub}@{fg text}

I talked to a friend (CRiViT) some time ago and he asked for a program that puts MiamiStart.rexx and MiamiStop.rexx into one script.  I had a look at the code, and it basically sucked dead camels.  After my hacking, I wrote one that was buggy, messy code, and not exactly working.  I ended leaving the project alone for many months.

I re-wrote it from scratch making it bug free and operational creating v2.00+.

After v2.05 I looked at MiamiControl. I noted his programming required a lot of work, and his error handling simply didn't exist.  I talked to him about such topics, he had no intension of adding such 'useless' things when I mentioned ways to improve his program.  As he put it, 'people get what they deserveif they try weird things'.


@{fg highlight}@{b}Purpose:@{ub}@{fg text}

To get you Load Miami, get online/offline/quit Miami with one button/menu item.  @{u}It even allows you to see your online time/connect speed after you reset@{uu}.

It also allows extensive & easy control and use of Miami's functions and features. Something which I have yet to see in any package in a good, fast manner.

It alerts you if the Main Miami Program or if Miami settings given does not exist, it works its best to get you online without much hassle.

It also starts programs you wish to run via a text file you can create and runs them @{u}only@{uu} once you are online (automatically or via choice) or at a press of button.

It handles all possible error situations, and possibilities.  Unlike the "supposed" competition.

An @{u}optional@{uu} GUI that can be told to stay up always so you can perform any action at any stage.

An expert option to remove explainations of options that you do not need to know.

I have made this to be a safe, workable and highly configurable program (from the low end user to the power user), so you can live and work with ease in your daily usage of Miami Start/Stop.

@Endnode
@Node Features "Features - Miami Start/Stop - Miami Online/Offline/Online Details/Program Launcher with GUI"
@{fg highlight}@{b}Miami Start/Stop Features:@{ub}@{fg text}

- Display connect speed.

- Online time which is reset proof.

- ReConnections after the initial connection for the current connection.

- Previous online connection time.

- Total connections, reconnections, passive offlines, and active offlines.

- Total online time for all connections, how long you have

- Full, 100% accurate Phone line costing for current, prior & total online time.

- ISP cost calculations for current, prior, total online time.

- Current and prior phone call & phone bill cost calculation.

- Minimum & Maximum online time and date they occured.

- Shows current system time on the online details (if you forget what time it is .. or loose track ;).

- Averages for per day, per weekday and per connection for all possible items listed above.

- Load, get online, offline, quit Miami with the choice of a setting file.

- Ability to 'check' any connection time in MiamiDx easily.

- A-Synchronous & two forms of Synchronous loading of the Miami phone log.

- Miami aware self altering/adaptive GUI. (Changes GUI according to what Miami/Version you run)

- Change Miami's GUI status in various ways.

- Highly Extensive Shell arguments support.

- Extensive external preferences editor.

- Preferences starter from within Miami Start/Stop with warnings if you are using an older/newer preferences editor.

- Startup/Shutdown script handling using a @{u}simple@{uu} 'smart' @{" language " link StartStop}.

- User definable delay between programs in Startup/Shutdown scripts.

- Fully definable Time/Date format.

- Ability to toggle expert menus (Smaller menus).

- User definable placement of the Menus upon the screen.

- User definable screen to open Miami Start/Stop upon.

- Ability to toggle Miami Quit/Offline verification.

- Ability to toggle Miami Auto-Online switch.

- Ability to toggle a switch to have Miami Start/Stop stay running all the time (with quit still available).

- Recovery and smart handling in situations where not enough information is known or available.

- Many, many more features.



@{u}@{b}Notes for people comparing Miami Start/Stop to MiamiControl:@{ub}@{uu}

Miami Start/Stop will protect itself and yourself from being disappointed when something was configured wrong/goes wrong. Protects you and the program from possible errors.

MiamiControl wastes CPU/HD time by doing its own file writing routines with Miami status.
Miami Start/Stop does @{b}NOT@{ub} waste CPU/HD time by doing its own file writing routines with the Miami online status.

MiamiControl waste memory and CPU time by opening numerous ports while running in the background
MiamiStart/Stop does @{b}NOT@{ub} waste memory and CPU time by opening numerous ports while running in the background.

MiamiControl cannot fully 'check' every connection time in MiamiDx.
Miami Start/Stop can use MiamiDx just as easy as the normal Miami.

MiamiControl can't be run numerous times if you wish to.
Miami Start/Stop can be run numerous times as you wish.

Miami Start/Stop Log File Analyser shows a lot more information then MiamiControl could ever dream of doing.

MiamiControl Phone Line Cost calculation is innacurate.
Miami Start/Stop is 100% accurate to Miami's own log.

This is just a very quick overview of the differences.


@Endnode
