            - Searches the Current Directory, then Miami and finally SYS:Prefs/ directory to run the MSSPrefs executable.  If all locations fail, it then asks the user to select MSSPrefs.
           Added secure MSSPrefs starting which will ONLY allow you to run MSSPrefs when you hit the Prefs button.
            (Does a byte analysis of the selected preferences to check if it is really MSSPrefs)
           Added security check of Miami Start/Stop Version when starting MSSPrefs from inside MSS.  It warns you of the different MSS version number, and if MSS is newer then MSSPrefs, it will not run a non MSSPrefs file.
           Added ';' as comment charcter for lines in your Startup or Shutdown files.  Place it at the the first charcter of a line in your MSS Startup or Shutdown script.
           Added Miami Start/Stop Menu opening location options: Top Left, Centre of screen, Follow Mouse.  Default: Follow Mouse.
           Added optional screen to open on.  If the screen is not available, MSS opens on the default public screen.
           Added Date(s) that the Min & Max online time happened.  EG: 'on 06/Dec/98 to 07/Dec/98'  or for a single day, 'on 02/Dec/98' as appropriate.
           Added Quick action switches: Details, Online, Offline, Quit & ForceQuit command line (CLI/Shell).  (Offline, Quit & ForceQuit will auto-enable verification of going offline)
            - These switches will not work if Miami is not in the right state.  EG: Details will not work if Miami is not loaded and online. Quit will not work if Miami isn't loaded.
           Added Lock, UnLock, KillGUI swiches to alter Miami's GUI status.
           Added 'Go @{u}B@{uu}ack' buttons to 'most' sub menus.
           Changed default setting of Verify to On!
           Added default selection in the Online menu of "@{u}L@{uu}oad" when you are not online and "@{u}O@{uu}k" when you are online with Miami.
           Added 'Error!' Menu notifying the user if an error occurs and to send the Author (his email address displayed) the problem Miami Phone Log.
           Added user configurable date format.  Total control is possible.  Fully smart!
           Added '@{u}O@{uu}ffline Menu' button to the Menu when Miami is loaded with Settings.
           Fixed Keyboard shortcuts on the Miami is loaded with current settings menu.

           If you have a Miami Phone Log active:
           Added various more average calculations including Reconnect averages for connection.
           Added Total Phone Line Charges and Total ISP Charges.
           Added Averages of phone line charges and ISP charges. (Will not show the average per connect if you pay a flat rate)
           Added ISP Charges and Phone Line Charges to Prior connect time.


v2.30    - Smart shutdown.  Makes even non arexx programmers able to comtrol programs via ARexx.
30/Oct/98  Fixed the excess wait after running all the programs/AREXX bits.
           Added Shutdown & NoShutdown @{" arguement " link Using} that will let you define from Shell the Shutdown file or if you wish to use No Shutdown file at all.
           Changed MSS so if Miami:Miami.default was found and no Miami settings argument was given. (Some people might dislike this change, sorry)
           Cleaned up the Menu's layout and design to handle the many extra features.

v2.08   -  Added backup use of Connect Speed from Miami's Phone Log if the user is using a buggy Miami version.
29/Oct/98  Added Miami Offline/Quit/ForceQuit check routine. Really useless as shit, but it is there now.
           Opytimised ReadArgs and various other points in the program.
           Sped up Miami Phone Log to Epoch routines.
           Added an @{b}EXTENSIVE@{ub} phone log analyser (@{b}Beat this MiamiControl@{ub} ;)
           Added LogTime/LogFile @{" arguement " link Using} to enable the full Log file analysation. (@{b}It slows logfile analysing drastically!@{ub})
           Added Miami Phone Log Total & Average Online Time to the phone log analyser under the LogTime @{" arguement " link Using}.
           Added Min/Max Online Time under the LogTime @{" arguement " link Using}.
           Added Cost analysis of the log file when using the LogTime @{" arguement " link Using} which is 100% accurate.
           Changed Online Details Menu display format.
           Added Reconnection(s) to the Online Details Menu if you use the Miami Phone log.
           Changed GUI buttons to be more universally conforming in their placement.
           @{u}Changed Time @{" arguement " link Using} to Seconds!@{uu}
           Added Verify @{" arguement " link Using} that will make sure if you wish to Disconnect/Quit/Force Quit.
           Fixed Inernet online costs to count current minute as a used minute.  As providers really charge you.
           Fixed Internet online costs to never show negative results.

           Fixed MSSPrefs default keys in the Main Menu.
           Fixed MSSPrefs Cancel when selecting a Log File will default to the old one.
           Fixed MSSPrefs LogFile Editted prefs routine.
           Fixed MSSPrefs old useless information.
           Optimised MSSPrefs performance generally.

v2.07    - Added Expert GUI that disables explainations of the general buttons.
14/Oct/98  Toggle switch for Expert mode under the GUI area to turn it On and Off on the fly.
           Made Miami Phone Log Checking Bullet Proof!
           Improved different Settings loaded in Miami to given ones GUI layout.
           Cleaned up the GUI code.
           Optimised code to use the same file opening code for various file opening places.
           Fixed startup bugs in Miami Start/Stop Prefs.
           Fixed .library loading in Miami Start/Stop Prefs.
           Removed CLI output in Miami Start/Stop Prefs.
           Removed CTCP/Msg question (from my old XDCC-get prefs code. Erk) in Miami Start/Stop Prefs.
           Cleaned up Verify Exit menu in Miami Start/Stop Prefs.

v2.06    - Handles unlimited resets without losing track of connect info when dealing with the Miami phone log.
14/Oct/98  More very secure handling of the Miami Phone Log.
           Drops back to getting details from Miami itself if the Miami phone log has problems.
           Altered the code to be a more robust design.
           Optimised the code slightly.
           Cleaned up the Guide file a bit.

v2.05    - Moved Miami Start/Stop into the stables of Omniscient International & Amiga Coding Syndicate (Kuang 11) groups.
11/Oct/98  Added Prefs editor for all the new functions of Miami Start/Stop.
           Added Time @{" arguement " link Using} to allow user definable delays between starting of programs. (Default is 250 Ticks, 50 Ticks = 1 second)
           Changed @{u}E@{uu}NV:MSS_Startup button to use 'E' as the shortcut key also as the default response, if it's there.
           Changed return to Offline Menu/Online Menu after warning window when you try to go online/offline when already that way.
           Improved handling of of when to choose a Startup File via the GUI.
           Removal of 'NoStartup' of programs when the user goes to the Full GUI Menu (Always/GUI) so they can start programs then.
           Fixed error windows to show up properly when a library was missing. (My own silly fault for optimising too far :)
           Added Provider Online Charges.  See @{" Install " link Using} on how to configure.
           Added Reset proof Connect time calculations.  See @{" Installation " link Install} on how to configure this.
           Improved Online time to remove Online Days & Hours if it is only 0 (Zero).

v2.02   -  Fixed Already Online/Offline/Miami not loaded Menu "@{u}G@{uu}UI" & "@{u}O@{uu}k" Buttons.
28/Sep/98  Fixed clash of shortcut keys "@{u}D@{uu}etails" & "@{u}D@{uu}epart"(D) on the Full Menu.
           Allocated shortcut key for "Online & Program@{u}s@{uu}"(S) on the Online Menu.
           Fixed telling of connection speed when not online with Miami. Now reports back: 0 bps. (Miami checked its internal working in 3.0d).
           Fixed Offline button when to report back now "You are already offline.".
           Fixed config file checking. Shows correct requestor when no setting was given in the arguments.
           Fixed "Load" button to work better with config handling.
           Added @{u}G@{uu}UI button to a menu which missed it when dealing with Miami Settings.
           Fixed the Config loading routine to be more easier to read and works a LOT better.
           Fixed loading of Programs when quitting Miami while waiting to see if online. (Miami locks it's ARexx port when it opens requestors)
           Fixed loading of programs twice if the user hit the "Wait More" button.
           Added workaround for the Miami 3.0d (and prior?) bug of 'GetOnlineTime' in the UnRegistered Miami.
           Added NotAutoOnline/NAO switches.  See @{" Usage " link Using} to see what they do.
           Added a delay between starting programs(200 Ticks, 50 Ticks = 1 second), so there is not so much head bashing when loading the programs.
           Added ENV:@{u}M@{uu}SS_Startup button if the file exists when No Startup file set or hitting the Programs button from a Menu.

v2.01    - Added a LOT of options.

v2.00    - Re-Write from scratch the program in hour.

v1.00    - Attempted fix, but the code was just too messy/badly laid out.

v0.99    - Buggy version from original idea.

